I think your negative sample set is a little biased. Since all the phrases start with verbs like "was in the car" or "went to the park", these kinds of phrases are given lower probabilities.<p>For example:<p><pre><code>    > twss.prob("was on a stiff pole");
    0.016050826334564946
</code></pre>
Only 1.6% chance of that's what she said?!?<p>EDIT: Counter example:<p><pre><code>    > twss.prob("that's one stiff pole");
    0.9767718880285885</code></pre>
